# usta-cli rules

Read [`AGENTS.md`](mdc:AGENTS.md) for the full rule set. The highlights:

- The module dependency rule is the law: `crate::core` ‚Üê `crate::ports` ‚Üê `crate::app` ‚Üê `crate::adapters` ‚Üê `crate::wiring`. Code review enforces; was Cargo-enforced before the v0.1.0 single-crate collapse.
- `crate::core` and `crate::ports` are I/O free. No `tokio`, no `reqwest`, no `git2`, no `std::fs`, no `std::process`.
- `crate::app` cannot import from `crate::adapters`.
- Concrete adapters are wired only in `src/wiring.rs`.
- `extract` is deterministic. No network LLM calls anywhere in the engine.
- New behavior goes behind a new trait (OCP). Traits stay narrow (ISP, ‚â§ 5 methods).
- Engine modules use `thiserror`. `anyhow` only at the binary boundary (main.rs, commands/, wiring.rs).
- Conventional Commits required. `cargo fmt --check`, `cargo clippy -D warnings`, `cargo test` must pass.
- Don't propose anything from [`docs/NON_GOALS.md`](mdc:docs/NON_GOALS.md) without an ADR.
- Path traversal: never write outside the resolved output directory.
- Update [`PLAN.md`](mdc:PLAN.md) as phases progress.
